Arya Architects – Frontend Web Project

Arya Architects is a modern and responsive frontend web application designed for showcasing architectural and interior design projects. The website provides an elegant user interface where users can explore different categories of architectural work including residential, commercial, interior design, sustainable projects, and renovation ideas.

The project focuses on creating a clean user experience with visually appealing layouts, project filtering functionality, smooth navigation, and responsive design principles.

Features

* Responsive navigation bar
* Project category filtering system
* Modern UI/UX design
* Interactive project showcase section
* Search functionality for projects
* Clean and structured layout
* Responsive design for multiple devices

Technologies Used

* HTML5
* CSS3
* JavaScript
* Responsive Web Design

Project Purpose

This project was created to improve frontend development skills and demonstrate practical implementation of responsive layouts, UI components, and interactive web design concepts.

Future Improvements

* Backend integration
* User authentication system
* Dynamic project management
* Contact form functionality
* Database connectivity
* Advanced animations and transitions

This project reflects my interest in frontend web development, user interface design, and creating visually engaging web applications.

